# Copy to ".env" in this folder, then restart: npm start
#
# If you omit mail settings and NODE_ENV is not "production", the server sends OTP
# via Ethereal (test inbox — a preview link opens in the browser). For real Gmail
# delivery to users, configure Gmail or SMTP below.
#
# --- Gmail (recommended) ---
# OTP emails are sent TO whatever address users enter at signup (including @gmail.com).
# GMAIL_USER / GMAIL_APP_PASSWORD are for the SERVER account that sends mail (can be the same Gmail or a dedicated noreply account).
#
# Use a Google "App password" (not your normal Gmail password):
# Google Account → Security → 2-Step Verification → App passwords → Mail / Other → generate 16 chars
GMAIL_USER=youraddress@gmail.com
GMAIL_APP_PASSWORD=xxxx xxxx xxxx xxxx

# Optional "From" name (defaults to MUST Quality + GMAIL_USER)
# SMTP_FROM="MUST Quality <youraddress@gmail.com>"

# --- Or generic SMTP (same Gmail values work here instead of GMAIL_* ) ---
# SMTP_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
# SMTP_PORT=587
# SMTP_SECURE=0
# SMTP_USER=youraddress@gmail.com
# SMTP_PASS=your-app-password
# SMTP_FROM="MUST Quality <youraddress@gmail.com>"
